FEMNET – a Pan-African Feminist Network of over 700 women’s rights organizations and individuals continues to promote women’s rights and the gender equality agenda.&#xd;
&#xd;
FEMNET is about mobilizing and connecting our members – strengthening their capacities to organize and participate effectively in the development processes at different levels in Africa.&#xd;
&#xd;
FEMNET is about informing and sharing ideas, experiences, strategies and models that are working for women’s empowerment and gender equality.&#xd;
&#xd;
Yes, FEMNET is about influencing policymakers and other actors to create an enabling environment and avail adequate resources for the realization of gender equality and women’s empowerment in Africa.&#xd;
&#xd;
FEMNET's members spans across 45 African countries in all the 5 sub-regions of Africa:-&#xd;
Northern Africa&#xd;
Eastern Africa&#xd;
Western Africa&#xd;
Central Africa&#xd;
